Rodong Sinmun Rips into Japanese Right-wing Conservatives' Rash Act 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 8 (KCNA) -- Japanese Prime Minister Koizumi, during his recent visit to Pyongyang, expressed his willingness to set store by the Japan-DPRK Pyongyang Declaration, turn the hostile relations into those of cooperation and put the bilateral relations on a normal track through the sincere implementation of the declaration.
 However, there are very unsavory developments in Japan which throw a dark shadow over the above-said efforts. Clear evidence of it was the passage of the reactionary "bill banning the portcall of specified foreign ships" through the House of Representatives of Japan in recent days. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A signed commentary of Rodong Sinmun Tuesday dismisses this as rowdyism which can be committed only by those wicked guys displeased with the DPRK-Japan summit meeting and its outcome. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japanese conservative right-wingers' call for tightened sanctions against the DPRK and pressure on it is a product of their moves to carry out the U.S. hostile policy to stifle the DPRK, the commentary notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was none other than the Japanese reactionaries who accepted the U.S. proposal for laying an international siege to the DPRK before anybody else and participated in the joint military exercises to intercept and seize its planes and ships. It is the purpose of the Japanese right-wing conservatives to get actively involved in the U.S. imperialists' moves and bring down the socialist system in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese right-wing conservatives' adoption of a new law calling for sanctions against the DPRK was prompted by their sinister intention to deliberately hamstring the implementation of the declaration in violation of the spirit of the DPRK-Japan summit talks and disregard of the commitments made by the Japanese prime minister. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With nothing can they justify their rash acts of going against the spirit of the meeting and the Pyongyang declaration, reneging on the bilateral commitments and good faith. The people's mind-set will certainly make them pay for what they have done. They are well advised to stop such foolish and reckless acts, bearing in mind the proverb as you sow, so shall you reap.

Implementation of June 15 Joint Declaration Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 8 (KCNA) -- The Korean nation is now in high spirits to win victory in the confrontation with the U.S. through practical actions. Yun Ki Jin, chairman of the South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification, said this in an appeal on June 3 on the occasion of the 4th anniversary of the publication of the June 15 joint declaration, calling upon the Korean nation to thoroughly implement the June 15 joint declaration.
 The appeal said: Let's pave a wide avenue for peace and reunification in the spirit of national independence. This is the theme of "the Koreans' meeting to mark the 4th anniversary of the publication of the June 15 joint declaration." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Let's make the June 15 function a festival for national cooperation against the U.S.
 This meeting should provide an opportunity of creating favorable conditions for the independent reunification of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal called for building a new reunified country by the concerted efforts and wisdom of the Koreans.

DPRK Also Has Option 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 8 (KCNA) -- Minju Joson in a commentary Tuesday raps at the shameless act of the Bush administration in trying to force upon the DPRK its unjustifiable demand regarding the nuclear issue with a threat of economic sanctions.
 Recalling that a high-ranking official of the Bush administration threatened that if the DPRK refused to accept the demand of the U.S. for "complete, verifiable and irreversible nuclear dismantlement," the nuclear issue would be taken to the UN Security Council so as to impose economic sanctions upon the DPRK, the news analyst goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "complete nuclear dismantlement" demanded by the U.S. is intended to realize its scheme of "disarmament first, overthrow of the system next" by robbing the DPRK of its nuclear deterrent without payment. Its call for "irreversible" and "verifiable" nuclear dismantlement is to stifle the DPRK economically by destroying its peaceful nuclear power industry and round off war preparations for stifling it by searching its inside with a toothcomb under the cloak of inspection. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  If the U.S. truly wanted a peaceful settlement of the nuclear issue, it should give up its robber-like demand and take a measure based on the principle of simultaneous action. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. can be settled peacefully by the mode of "word to word" and "action to action" based on the principle of simultaneous action to suit its character and the present situation. The U.S. must take a concrete measure to carry into practice the proposal of the DPRK for "compensation to freezing."  Should the U.S., shunning this proposal, try to force upon the DPRK its demand for "complete, verifiable and irreversible nuclear dismantlement" with "written assurances of security," a mere sheet of paper, the DPRK will also demand a verifiable complete withdrawal of the U.S. forces from south Korea and "complete, verifiable and irreversible assurances of security" which would be guaranteed by the signing of a peace agreement and normalization of relations between the two sides. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Option is not a monopoly of the U.S. The DPRK also has it.

Kim Jong Il, Rare Elder Statesman 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 8 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il possessed of distinguished political ability and rich experience is the peerlessly great man who is leading the 21st century, says Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed article.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exploits performed by Kim Jong Il in the last four decades cover all the fields of the revolution and construction including party, state, army and cultural building and each of them is a precious guideline of the developing revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 40 year-long history of his leadership over the revolution is a precious wealth of the Korean revolution. Particularly, over the last ten years when he has left immortal revolutionary records by leading the Korean army and people have been significant days when his political ability has been displayed to the full. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The greatness of Kim Jong Il who has recorded an ever-victorious history of leadership over the revolution lies in creating a brilliant example of independent politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Independence is his political philosophy and the fundamental principle which runs through his politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has led the Korean revolution from the steadfast stand of thinking and acting always with one's own reason and solving all the matters arising in the revolutionary struggle and state building by the efforts of the people in the interests of the Korean revolution and in conformity with the specific conditions of the country according to one's own view and faith. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The struggle to defend socialism in the past ten years in particular is a shining chronicle in which it has emerged victorious thanks to his independent politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The greatness of Kim Jong Il who has recorded an ever-victorious history of leadership over revolution lies in his creation of a model of benevolent politics. Benevolence is the basis of his politics. It is his creed that revolution is immediately love for the people and politics is to love and take care of them, not to rule them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His greatness also lies in that he opened a new era of Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Basing himself on a scientific analysis of the characteristics of the socialist cause which is advancing in constant confrontation with the U.S. imperialists and the revolutionary role of the People's Army in the developing era, he set forth the original mode of Songun politics to advance the revolution with the People's Army as the main force and pillar of revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underlying his distinguished political ability as a rare elder statesman is his personality as a great man. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His high sense of responsibility and mission for the destiny of the country and the people is the main factor of his ever-victorious history of leadership over the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His extraordinary resources and far-sightedness are the basic guarantee for his ever-victorious history of leadership over the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His political faith and iron will are the decisive factors of his brilliant ever-victorious history of leadership over the revolution.

Japan's Legislation against DPRK Denounced in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 8 (KCNA) -- A commentary was published on June 3 by the south Korean Internet radio "People's Voice" upon the passage of the "bill banning the entry of specified foreign ships into port" through the Japanese Diet.
 Recalling that the bill was at last carried through the Japanese lower house, the commentary says: This is a quite crude act devoid of faith like hitting one's head on the back after smiling in his face. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The passage of a series of bills on sanctions against the DPRK through the Japanese Diet is intended to create tension by getting on the nerves of the DPRK and justify the revision of the constitution, notes the commentary, and adds: Now the insane drift to the right of the Japanese rightist conservatives is past the danger line. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan ignorant of faith between countries can never be pardoned. If the south and the north of Korea merge voice in condemning its hostile policy towards the DPRK, this would deal a decisive blow to its madcap drift to the Right.

Increasing U.S. Pressure upon S. Korea over Issue of Its New Embassy Premises 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 8 (KCNA) -- The United States is increasing its pressure upon south Korea to meet its request for building its new embassy premises in the Ryongsan base.
 The U.S. had announced that its Ryongsan base would be transferred to Phyongthaek by the end of 2006, but it is now seeking to build its new embassy premises in that place instead of returning it to s. Korea without any condition. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. plan to expand its embassy premises has long been in the making. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. pressurized the south Korean authorities to offer the site of the Toksu Palace, a national cultural heritage, as a building lot for its embassy early in the1980s and has since pushed forward the plan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On July 26, 2002, the U.S. ambassador to south Korea once again disclosed the U.S. intention to go ahead with its plan to build new embassy premises, asserting that it is desirable to have new embassy premises in the heart of Seoul and it is right to build new embassy premises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The U.S. said it would construct a 15-storeyed building of the embassy, an 8-storeyed apartment house for embassy officials and a 4-storeyed quarters for U.S. troops, their floor space totaling over 54,900 square meters, in the site of the Toksu Palace located in the area of Jongdong, Central District, Seoul. Then it urged the south Korean authorities to render active cooperation in this matter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S., however, failed to achieve this aim in face of the strong protest from different circles in south Korea. As the U.S. was compelled to transfer its base in Ryongsan to Phyongthaek, it came out with a plan to build its embassy premises covering 67,000 phyong in that place and has since zealously egged pro-American forces on to help in this matter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If this thing is allowed to happen, the U.S. would still have at its disposal a total of 100,000 phyong of land including the areas to be used as embassy premises and a liaison office of its forces even after the return of its base in Ryongsan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean people are conducting activities to retake all the area of the U.S. base in Ryongsan and turn it into a national park, branding the U.S. moves as an unpardonable mockery of the Koreans' self-esteem.

Political Guidelines for 17th-term S. Korean National Assembly Proposed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 8 (KCNA) -- The Democratic Workers' Party of south Korea called a press conference on June 4 at which it proposed political guidelines for the 17th-term National Assembly, according to the south Korean KBS.
 The four-point guidelines advanced by National Assemblymen from the Democratic Workers' Party call for narrowing the gap between the rich and the poor, abolishing such anti-democratic draconic law as the Security Law, protecting the rights to food and achieving peace on the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
They evinced their determination to work hard to implement these tasks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They underscored the need for the 17th-term NA to focus its efforts on withdrawing the motion on additional troop dispatch to Iraq, reforming politics and the National Assembly, stopping the discrimination against the part-time workers and opposing the opening of local rice market and the construction of a dumping ground of nuclear waste.

Preserving Spirit of National Independence Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 8 (KCNA) -- The historic Pyongyang meeting and the adoption of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration was a historic event of the Korean nation as it instilled confidence and optimism about national reunification into all Koreans in the north, the south and overseas and raised a hot wind of reunification throughout Korea. Rodong Sinmun Tuesday says this in a signed article.
 It is the great result of the Pyongyang meeting and the June 15 joint declaration that the nation set forth independence as a common ideal and a militant banner for the north and the south, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The principle of national independence is the core issue of solving national issues and a basic principle to be adhered to in the struggle for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The issue of Korean reunification is, in essence, one of establishing national sovereignty throughout Korea, rejoining the blood ties of the Koreans separated in the north and the south and achieving national unity. Korea should be, therefore, reunified by the concerted efforts of its people without allowing any foreign forces to interfere in them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The cause of national reunification calls on all Koreans to independently solve all issues as a master in line with their will and interests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The principle of national independence is vital to national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
If foreign forces are allowed to interfere in the issue of national reunification, the issue of retaking the usurped national sovereignty, it will complicate the issue and lead to nothing but a catastrophic situation after all. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The principle of national independence serves as a sure guarantee for strengthening the driving force and increasing its role in carrying out the cause of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Though all the Koreans form a driving force of national reunification its might does not get strong by itself. It can prove strong only when all the members of the nation unite as one, highly aware of being responsible for the reunification movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The success made by the Korean nation in implementing the historic June 15 joint declaration for the last 4 years proves that the principle of independence serves as a banner of unity and a fundamental idea of accelerating the independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that it is the unanimous will of the Korean people desirous of independent reunification to hold aloft the banner of national independence, the article stresses that the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration serves as the only treasured sword enabling the Koreans to achieve national reunification as it calls for settling the issue of the country's reunification independently free from any foreign interference.

Appeal to S. Koreans
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 8 (KCNA) -- The British Group for the Study of the Juche Idea - Works of Comrade Kim Jong Il, the British Society for the Study of Songun Politics, the Group for the Study of Songun Politics in the U.S. and the All Anti-Imperialists Wishing to Build Solidarity with the DPRK in the U.S. issued a joint appeal to the south Koreans on May 26.
 The appeal referred to the anti-U.S. struggle that swept all parts of south Korea in the wake of GIs' murder of two young schoolgirls two years ago. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It accused the U.S. of making frantic preparations to launch the second Korean war in a bid to exterminate the Korean nation under the pretext of the nuclear issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal said: Today the destiny of not only south Koreans but all other Koreans has been seriously jeopardized by the U.S. This grim reality calls upon all the Koreans in the north and the south to turn out as one in a nationwide anti-U.S. struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans have strength and conditions enough to defeat the U.S. on a nationwide scale. The DPRK is making a victorious advance thanks to the might of Songun and south Korea is witnessing an astonishing political reality in which the popular masses desirous of the new are emerging victorious and successfully meeting the challenge of the U.S. and the reactionary forces in unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal called upon all the patriotic-minded south Koreans to put an end to the U.S. imperialists' colonial rule over south Korea, turn out in a struggle to completely remove the root cause of war from the Korean peninsula and uphold the great Songun politics in the same spirit with which they won in the general election. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The followers of the Songun idea and anti-imperialist fighters in the U.S. and Britain are firmly convinced that the south Koreans who have a tradition of the heroic anti-U.S. struggle will certainly emerge victorious in the struggle to bring about a new society and a new history of independence and reunification free from the U.S. imperialist aggressor forces under the banner of the great Songun politics and the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration.

Russian Ensemble's Performance Goes on
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 8 (KCNA) -- The performance of the State Academy Ensemble of the Ministry of Interior of Russia on a visit to the DPRK goes on at the Ponghwa Art Theatre.
 On June 7 people from all walks of life in Pyongyang saw the performance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ensemble made up of scores of people's artistes, merited artistes and international concours winners proved to be a famous art troupe through its performance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its repertoire that began with the chorus of immortal revolutionary paean "Song of General Kim Il Sung" included wartime songs reflecting the patriotic spirit of Russians, famous songs of the DPRK, Russia and Italy such as "Song of the Sea," "Kalinka" and Kalaf's Aria from drama "Trandot," national instrumental solo, chorus, mixed duet, dances and other colorful pieces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Male quartet of Academician, Prof. and People's Artiste Viktor Eliseyev who is head of the ensemble and head conductor, People's Artiste Grigori Pinyasov, Merited Artiste Viktor Gromov and Artiste Sergei Titov and chorus "Song of Stenka Razin", female solo of Merited Artiste Nataliya Kurganskaya and chorus "Swan", male solo of People's Artiste Vladimir Romanov and chorus "Marusha" and other songs were highly acclaimed by the audience for the refined vocal talent of precentors, well-organized ensemble of the players and singers and a high level of their representation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The artistes also staged national instrumental solo "Lark," male solo and chorus "Along the Bank of the River Volga" and "My Dearest" and "Dance of Victory" and "Dance of Kazaks" and other  colorful numbers reflecting the national sentiment and optimistic and cheerful life of the Russians, beautifully decorating the stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They touched the heartstrings of the audience by singing well famous Korean songs such as "Song Devoted to Comrade Kim Jong Il," " My Blessed Life", "My Native Place", etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance continues.

Schoolchildren's Vocal Music Training Centre
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 8 KCNA) -- The schoolchildren's vocal music training center at Pyongyang Pothonggang Middle School plays a big role in training singers in the country.
 The centre, set up in Juche 72 (1983), gives vocal lessons to schoolchildren selected from schools in the city. Their lessons include such scientific vocal principles and methods as basic music theories, sound detection and sight reading. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the past two decades the centre has trained many talented singers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Among them are Ri Hyang Suk, a soprano who won the top prize at the 11th Giuseppe di Stefano International Concours, and Paek Mi Yong, who proved successful at the Maria Canilia International Vocal Music Concours held in Itay in last October. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many of those who were trained in the centre are now active in the State Merited Chorus of the Korean People's Army, the Pochonbo Electronic Band, the Wangjaesan Light Music Ensemble, Phibada Opera Troupe and other major art troupes.
